    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-18T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 18—3:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. Department’s 413, November 12, 6 p.m.<note n="46" xml:id="d397fn46">Not
                        printed.</note> Department’s November 12, 6 p.m., to Peking was read to
                    Foreign Office today which stated that the reply of the British Government to
                    the French representations made here was in substance identical with the reply
                    of Secretary Hughes. Foreign Office added you may sum up our position in the
                    words, “We agree with the diplomatic body in Peking in a wait and see
                    attitude.”</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
